{"TopicId":139046,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"[Request] Aerobraking Baloons","CreatedByName":"kinnison","CreatedById":68083,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-05T14:49:07Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"kinnison","CreatedById":68083,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-05T14:49:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the Movie \u00222010\u0022 the Lenov uses aerobraking to decelerate on it\u0027s approach to Jupiter.\u00A0 The craft deploys disposable Ballons to aid in protecting the craft.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/ibf-6O3uU6Q?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022459\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf i had any skill at Modding I would do it myself.\u00A0 But i like this idea to have something inflatable to protect the craft when needed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-05-05T14:49:28Z\u0022 title=\u002205/05/2016 02:49  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMay 5, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by kinnison\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex_NL","CreatedById":58254,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-05T14:54:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomething like this perhaps?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/121162-110-inline-ballutes-ib-v124-2842016/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kinnison","CreatedById":68083,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-05T19:36:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope.\u00A0 Those are used like Parachutes.\u00A0 Looking for something that works more like a heat shield\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nli2work","CreatedById":106805,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-05T20:04:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/76169-11-usi-survivability-pack-formerly-derp-v040/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceMouse","CreatedById":126931,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-05T21:04:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey literally call them ballutes in the video. Roverdude\u0027s survivability pack also includes baloons for landing but they MIGHT work for aerobraking as well. Vanilla 1.1 KSP also includes a very nifty inflatable heat shield that can also be used for the purpose.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nli2work","CreatedById":106805,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-05T22:45:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUSI\u0027s lithobraking balloon are the closest to what the OP is after... probably needs a little tinkering with the thermal properties.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}